description: Giant insect specimens, including an ant and a mosquito, are impaled on large pins, towering over two much smaller, wide-eyed ants on the floor below. The scene presents a surreal environment where the scale is inverted, making the preserved dead a source of fear for the living. This creates an absurd situation where navigating a seemingly ordinary space becomes terrifying due to the presence of oversized, deceased relatives. The small ants' perspective highlights the irony of being intimidated by static, harmless objects. The overall effect is one of unease and dark humor derived from this inversion of the natural order.
caption: “Gad, I hate walking through this place at night.”
